  "description": "Tax and reporting rules for employers providing gifts to employees",
  "details": {
    "body": "\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>As an employer providing gifts to your employees, you have certain tax, National Insurance and reporting obligations.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2 id=\"businesses\">Businesses</h2>\n\n<p>There are different rules depending on the type of gift you give. Follow the reporting and payment <a href=\"/expenses-and-benefits-a-to-z\" title=\"Expenses and benefits A to Z\">rules for the specific item</a>.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"self-employed\">Self-employed</h2>\n\n<p>If you’re self-employed, you don’t have to report or pay tax or National Insurance on personal gifts (eg birthday or wedding presents) that you give to employees.</p>\n\n",
    "external_related_links": [

    ]
  },
